quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  47,1,"Those who do not believe and turn away (people) from the way of God, He makes their deeds get lost"
  47,2,"And those who believe and do righteous works and believe in that which is sent down on Muhammad, and that is the truth from their Lord, He removes from them their evils and sets right their condition"
  47,3,That is because those who do not believe follow falsehood and those who believe follow the truth from their Lord. Thus God sets forth for mankind their similitudes
  47,4,"So when you meet the disbelievers ˹in battle˺, strike ˹their˺ necks until you have thoroughly subdued them, then bind them firmly. Later ˹free them either as˺ an act of grace or by ransom until the war comes to an end. So will it be. Had God willed, He ˹Himself˺ could have inflicted punishment on them. But He does ˹this only to˺ test some of you by means of others. And those who are martyred in the cause of God, He will never render their deeds void"
  47,5,He will guide them and set right their condition
  47,6,And He will make them enter the garden which He has made known to them
  47,7,"O you who believe! if you help God, He will help you and make your feet firm"
  47,8,"And those who do not believe, there is destruction for them and He makes their deeds get lost"
  47,9,"That is because they disliked that which God sent down, so He made their deeds become fruitless"
  47,10,"Have they not then traveled in the earth and seen, how the end of those before them was (brought about)? God brought down destruction upon them and for (these) disbelievers (too, there will be something) similar to it"
  47,11,"That is because God is the Guardian of those who believe, and because the disbelievers have no guardian for them"